This session is being continued from a previous conversation that ran out of context. The summary below covers the earlier portion of the conversation.

Summary:
1. Primary Request and Intent:

The user had three main requests across the conversation:

**Request 1**: Fix errors preventing webinar creation, video hosting, and video uploading from working at all.

**Request 2**: Verify whether the entire video marketing section (webinars + video hosting) works properly end-to-end.

**Request 3**: "Fix all the errors in the video marketing thing. I want people to host videos and host webinars properly." — fix all identified broken pieces so the platform is fully functional.

---

2. Key Technical Concepts:
- **Oravini** — Creator Growth Platform (SaaS), React + Express + PostgreSQL + Drizzle ORM, deployed on Render
- **WebRTC** — P2P video streaming from host to viewers via ICE/STUN/TURN servers (Google STUN + openrelay.metered.ca TURN)
- **WebSocket (ws library)** — signaling relay for WebRTC + real-time chat, Q&A, polls, CTAs, reactions
- **Webinar room pattern** — server-side `Map<webinarId, { host: WebSocket | null, viewers: Map<viewerId, {ws, name}> }>` for routing messages
- **Multer** — file upload middleware; two instances: `upload` (50MB general) and `videoUpload` (200MB, video/audio only)
- **HLS.js** — browser-side HLS stream player for broadcast URL mode
- **JIC (Just-In-Case) mode** — automated webinar where a pre-recorded video plays as if live
- **Drizzle ORM** — `sqlExpr` used for SQL increment expressions
- **TanStack Query** — `useQuery`/`useMutation` for all API calls with query key invalidation
- **wouter** — client-side routing library (used instead of React Router)
- **shadcn/ui + Tailwind** — component and styling library; dark theme, gold accent `#d4b461`
- **Lead gate** — email capture form shown before video plays when `leadGateEnabled` is true
- **Blob URL problem** — `URL.createObjectURL()` creates browser-local URLs that can't be stored or served

---

3. Files and Code Sections:

**`/Users/aryansurana/server/routes.ts`** (main server routes, ~11k+ lines)
- Most important file — multiple critical fixes applied here
- **Fix 1**: Replaced the minimal WebSocket handler with a full webinar room system:
```typescript
const webinarRooms = new Map<string, { host: WebSocket | null; viewers: Map<string, { ws: WebSocket; name: string }> }>();

function getOrCreateRoom(webinarId: string) { ... }
function broadcastToViewers(webinarId: string, data: object) { ... }

wss.on("connection", (ws, req) => {
  let currentRoom: string | null = null;
  let currentRole: "host" | "viewer" | null = null;
  let currentViewerId: string | null = null;

  ws.on("message", (raw) => {
    const msg = JSON.parse(raw.toString());
    const { type, webinarId } = msg;
    switch (type) {
      case "wr_host_join": room.host = ws; ws.send({type:"wr_host_ready"}); break;
      case "wr_offer": relay offer sdp to specific viewer; break;
      case "wr_ice_host": relay ICE candidate to viewer; break;
      case "wr_viewer_join": add viewer, notify host with wr_viewer_joined + wr_attendee_update; break;
      case "wr_answer": relay answer sdp to host; break;
      case "wr_ice_viewer": relay ICE candidate to host; break;
      case "wr_chat": route from viewer→host+others, or from host→all viewers; break;
      case "wr_qa": forward to host; break;
      case "wr_reaction": broadcast to all; break;
      case "wr_cta_launch": broadcastToViewers wr_cta_show; break;
      case "wr_cta_hide": broadcastToViewers wr_cta_hidden; break;
      case "wr_poll_launch": broadcastToViewers wr_poll_show; break;
      case "wr_poll_end": broadcastToViewers wr_poll_ended; break;
      case "wr_raise_hand": forward to host; break;
      case "wr_lower_hand": relay wr_hand_lowered to specific viewer; break;
      case "wr_host_end": broadcastToViewers wr_host_left, cleanup room; break;
    }
  });
  ws.on("close", () => { cleanup room membership, notify host of updated attendee count });
});
```
- **Fix 2**: Added `GET /api/webinars/public/:code` before the `:id` route:
```typescript
app.get("/api/webinars/public/:code", async (req, res) => {
  const webinar = await storage.getWebinarByMeetingCode(p(req.params.code));
  if (!webinar) return res.status(404).json({ message: "Webinar not found" });
  res.json(webinar);
});
```
- **Fix 3**: Added `POST /api/webinars/:id/recording/upload` using videoUpload multer:
```typescript
app.post("/api/webinars/:id/recording/upload", requireAuth, videoUpload.single("file"), async (req: any, res) => {
  const recordingUrl = `/uploads/${req.file.filename}`;
  const rec = await storage.createWebinarRecording({ webinarId, userId, title, recordingUrl, duration, fileSize, shareToken, isPublic: false });
  res.status(201).json(rec);
});
```
- **Fix 4**: Added `POST /api/upload/video` endpoint:
```typescript
app.post("/api/upload/video", requireAuth, videoUpload.single("file"), async (req: any, res) => {
  const videoUrl = `/uploads/${req.file.filename}`;
  res.json({ url: videoUrl, filename: req.file.filename, size: req.file.size });
});
```
- **New routes added** (all after `GET /api/video-events/:id`):
  - `GET /api/video/:id/public` — strips userId/passwordHash/domainWhitelist before returning
  - `GET /api/video/:id/chapters` — public chapters
  - `GET /api/video/:id/ctas` — public active CTAs only
  - `POST /api/video/:id/gate` — stores viewer session with `visitorId: email`, `referrer: "lead_gate:name"`
  - `POST /api/video-events/:id/view` — calls `storage.incrementVideoViews()`
  - `GET /api/video-marketing-settings` — returns user's Livekit settings
  - `PATCH /api/video-marketing-settings` — upserts via `storage.upsertVideoMarketingSettings()`
  - `GET /api/webinar-domains` — user's custom domains
  - `POST /api/webinar-domains` — creates with auto-generated `verifyToken`
  - `PATCH /api/webinar-domains/:id` — update domain
